<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <%- include('./partials/head.ejs') %>
  <body style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: monospace; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center;">
    <%- include('./partials/nav.ejs') %>
    <h1 style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px;">CRYPTWES API</h1>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: row; justify-content: center; gap: 50px; margin-top: 20px;">
      <div class="content" style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center;">
        <% for (let i = 0; i < CRYPTWES.length; i++) { %>
          <div style="background-color: rgb(255, 208, 0); margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: monospace; text-align: center; margin: 25px; border-radius: 10px;">
            <h4><%= CRYPTWES[i].name %>:</h4>
            <b><h3>(<%= CRYPTWES[i].sym %>)</h3></b>
            <p>Market cap of <%= CRYPTWES[i].name %> is: <%= CRYPTWES[i].cap.toFixed(2) %> USD</p>
          </div>
        <% } %> 
      </div>

      <div class="container" style="max-width: 40%; padding: 20px; margin-top: 20px; text-align: justify;">
        <div class="data-explanation">
          <h2 style="text-align: center;">CRYPTWES JSON Structure</h2>
          <div style="margin-left: 20px;">
            <p>The CRYPTWES array contains information about cryptocurrencies, including their name, symbol, and market capacity. Each element in the array is an object with the following key-value pairs:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><code>name</code>: The name of the cryptocurrency.</li>
              <li><code>sym</code>: The symbol associated with the cryptocurrency.</li>
              <li><code>cap</code>: The market capacity of the cryptocurrency.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 style="margin-left: 20px;">Example:</h3>
          <pre style="margin-left: 20px;">
            CRYPTWES: [
              { "name": "Bitcoin", "sym": "BTC", "cap": "1234567890" },
              { "name": "Ethereum", "sym": "ETH", "cap": "9876543210" },
              { "name": "Ripple", "sym": "XRP", "cap": "2468101214" },
              ...
            ]
          </pre>

          <h2 style="margin-top: 30px; text-align: center;">Accessing the CRYPTWES JSON Data</h2>
          <div style="margin-left: 20px;">
            <p>To access the JSON data, send a GET request to the appropriate API endpoint. The response will contain the CRYPTWES array in the JSON format, which can then be parsed and used in your application.</p>
          </div>

          <h3 style="margin-left: 20px;">Example API Endpoint:</h3>
          <pre style="margin-left: 20px;">GET /api/cryptocurrencies</pre>

          <h3 style="margin-left: 20px;">Response:</h3>
          <pre style="margin-left: 20px;">
            {
              "CRYPTWES": [
                { "name": "Bitcoin", "sym": "BTC", "cap": "1234567890" },
                { "name": "Ethereum", "sym": "ETH", "cap": "9876543210" },
                { "name": "Ripple", "sym": "XRP", "cap": "2468101214" },
                ...
              ]
            }
          </pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <%- include('./partials/footer.ejs') %>
  </body>
</html>
